<Content>Terrific hardware, nice big bright screen, good audio, easy to navigate controls, decent earphones.  Since MS is phasing out the 30 GB ones, look for bargains and DO NOT pay over $125 for these. Now the bad part - Zune software is basically an updated version of Windows Media Player. You need to be an experienced Windows user to get around the software easily.  Important tasks like syncing with your computer or setting up playlists isn't very intuitive.  If you want to download your favorite videos (including movies), you need to be VERY familier with video format conversions.  You can download a terrific free software for your computer to convery video to mp4 calle MediaCell Video Converter.     
