<Content>Microsoft Zune: What is not to like?  I picked this Brown 30 gig Gen 1 device up at Costco for under $100.   I am not going to say setup was without its issues. I initially had some problems but I updated my media server which is XP Media Center using the Microsoft Update website and reinstalled and that seemed to take care of the crashes and whatnot.  When you install Zune software from the CD in the package it automatically updated it to the latest and greatest firmware and software which allows full wireless sync like their 2nd generation products.  I have 20 gigs of 6 gigs of photos so I figured I'd be OK. It took most of an afternoon to get them uploaded but when I did I still had a bit over 9 gigs left on the Zune!  Next came the wireless setup. I have a D-Link `N' class router with WPA2 and AES encryption so I figured I'd have to bring down the encryption a tad. Not so! I just changed the settings to allow B, G and N class wireless traffic and allow WPA and WPA2 traffic (which means that my clients are still about as secure as you can get a home network) and volia!   I just logged into my media server and set up a playlist and fired up my Zune. In about 30 seconds I got the new play list sent over.  The sound quality is quite good and the pictures are petty good for a small screen as well!   
