<Content>I love this MP3 Player. The only problem I had was that when I started, I tried to plug it into my 4 port USB hub. The Zune needs power from a rear USB port. If you start out knowing that, you should be fine. The Zune holds music, video, pictures and podcasts. My computer transferred the music very quickly. But then my computer has a 3ghz dual core processor with 4gigs of RAM. The software installs easily and the Zune wiil take 3 hours to charge up. When you are using the Zune, it scrolls through the music very fast, no pauses when you are looking for a certain artist. You can add to the Zune on song at a time, multiple songs at a time, a hole album at once or even a while artist or multiple artists at once. You have the option to sync with your computer or not to sync with your computer. I have high speed internet, so the Zune updated to the current software quickly and smoothly. I really like it and I got it for $99 new, so it was a real bargain. I would suggest it to someone looking to get an MP3 player because it has so much space for a reasonable price.  
