<Review ID>6103860
<Product Name>Zune 30 GB Digital Media Player (White)
<Title>Love it!
<Date>Tue Oct 30 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I love this thing! My other mp3 player is a Creative Labs Nomad 60gig player.  I think that Creative Labs makes the best players out there, but the old one I have is a bit clunky weighs quite a bit. I bought this one because I decided I wanted the capability of video and it was on sale-- much lower than the price of One hundred thirty nine that it's on sale for now. The newer ones, at 80gbs, are coming out in a week or so, and this is why I bought this close-out model.  It came completely updated with the new firmware that will be on the newer ones.    Once you get it to work, it works very well. The software is very clunky, however. It makes my newer computer work very very hard when it is running.  iTunes doesn't do this, nor do some other programs I run, including Creative Labs software.  I really hate the Zune software, but it does work and it is pretty intuitive. That said, I need to stress that despite the fact that it IS intuitive, it didn't work correctly when I first started. Once I checked other message boards for specific answers to questions, it worked well and as it should.  However, I could not get my Zune to sync properly initially.  Two things I found very important:  First, make sure you use the back USB port on your computer, not the front. I didn't believe this could ever be an issue even though I knew that the front port gave off less power.  However, it couldn't even see my Zune when I used the front port. When I used the back port, it immediately recognized the player.  Secondly, when you set up your Zune for the first time, make sure you do not set it to automatically sync unless you are certain that is what you want it to do.  I have so many music files on my computer and there is no way they can all fit on  30 gb of space.  If it is set on automatically syncing, it will just fill up the Zune with the first 30 gigs, and the rest of my music will be unable to fit on there.  The player works really well and it's user friendly.  I am not sure about the battery life-- I don't think I've been getting the full time, but I'm not sure.  I plug it in when I listen to it at home and have only used it without a power adapter in the car which rarely amounts to a huge amount of time.  However, I am waiting for an additional cable so that I can leave on in the car and power it up to save the battery time.  
<Overall>4

