<Title>Zune 
<Date>Fri Aug 24 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>To the point...  First off, you can program the Zune software so that it doesn't pop up when you connect your Zune player to your computer.    Go to:  &lt;Options> &lt;Sync> Deselect or select the options you want off or on.  Secondly, I read a review where the reviewer said that the Zune will not recharge unless the computer is on.  This is not true.  Your Zune will recharge without your computer being on through the USB port.  The problem for some is that the Zune did not come with a manual or guide.  However, I find the lack of a manual refreshing, because it forced me to discover the little nuances of this product on my own, which for me is fun.  When I bought mine I had problems installing the software on Vista Ultimate, but no problem installing it on XP.  After I finally got the software installed on VU, I couldn't figure out how to download music (the one gripe I do have is not being able to drag and drop from outside the Zune Media software).  Phone support for the Zune has been great.  I called in with questions twice, got right through, and the support team walked me through a resolution both times easily.  Bottome line - I love this product.  Sound quality is superb which is, as far as I am concerned the main reason to buy an MP3 player.  The battery life does suck, but at least I'm not recharging AAA batteries any more.  I teach Spin classes (Indoor Cycling) at YMCA's and Golds gyms and the Zune with its large storage and great sound is perfect for that.  Gregg J.  
