<Content>I own several iPods.  To be honest, for my workouts I do prefer to use my shuffle for obvious reasons.  But the Zune in terms of home, office, car, and travel is just the coolest.  Yes, the software is a bit different and yes, if you are used to iTunes you will think it's difficult at first but within a day of palying around with it I was pretty tuned in on how to use.  The fact that you can download all you want for about $16 a month is perfect for people who purchase a lot of music.  With the ability to connect MP3s to virtually anything now, why should I purchase?  Saves a ton of money and find pretty much everything I want on Zune.  ALSO, if you do want to purchase from Zune, songs are only 79 cents compared to 99 cents on most other sites. Small but can add up if you do want to purchase a lot.  And then I don't have to transfer everyting via CD from iTunes. Goes right into my music library.  The screen is great quality too and I've had a chance to see what's coming out over the next year and they will have some smaller devices etc.  As I've seen in other comments, Zune will catch up.  I mean, remember the first iPod?  But bottom line, if you are a die hard iPod person then it's not for you.  If you're looking for something better for universal use, this is the ticket.  I love mine!  
